column211:
12/Jan/17 3:35 PM;tlong;Events are records that can be added to calendars and contain:
{code}
/**
Event Types:
Single
Recurring, Bounded
Recurring, Unbounded
*/

// Events
interface event {
	_id: "<auto generated>";
	time_start: int;
	time_end: int;
	name: string;
	description: string;
	// Recurring Only
	recurrence?: {
		bound_lower: int;
		bound_upper: int;		
	}
}

// Occurrences
interface ocurrance {
	_id: "<auto>";
	event: ObjectId() | null;
	time_start: int;
	time_end: int;

}
{code}

This data model and calendar is built on the materialized event concept. Instead of computing the entire universe of recurring events they will be written out to the DB periodically (Occurrences). This solves many of the use cases for normal calendar systems.

A few:
- recurrence on any schedule
- remove single occurance
- edit single occurance
- edit series without replacing removed ocurrances (non schedule data only)
- edit occurance and prevent updates from series (non schedule data only)

This interface does not outline how to store the recurring profiles, only how to store events. For recurring rules we should follow something like CalDAV or the ical formats.
